&lt;p&gt;Civitas Learning is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Quality Assurance Automation Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to join a talented, mission-driven team building powerful tools that greatly increase student success. Our QA team is collaborative, encouraged to bring new ideas, and pragmatic about tooling — we use the right tool for the job. We are problem solvers who want teammates passionate about our mission and eager to be part of a rapidly expanding, high-performance team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a traditional manual-only QA role. We run an &lt;strong&gt;AI-agent-orchestrated QA lifecycle&lt;/strong&gt;: test specs are drafted from Jira tickets and PR diffs, test cases and Playwright automation are generated with AI assistants, tests execute through browser automation with agentic failure triage, and results flow back to Jira and our test-management system automatically. You will not just write and run tests — you will &lt;strong&gt;curate, review, and improve the AI-assisted pipeline that produces them&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you&#39;ll do as a Quality Assurance Automation Analyst:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design detailed, comprehensive, well-structured test scenarios and test cases; analyze manual scenarios for automation candidacy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain &lt;strong&gt;Playwright&lt;/strong&gt; end-to-end automation, using AI assistants to accelerate test-script generation and applying self-healing locator strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, validate, and correct AI-generated test artifacts (specs, cases, automation) for correctness and coverage — treat AI output as a draft to verify, not a finished result.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage test cases and cycles in a test-management system and keep automation status reconciled.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debug, reproduce, and log bugs using QA tooling; triage automation failures (confirmed bug vs. flaky vs. environment).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write &lt;strong&gt;SQL&lt;/strong&gt; to validate back-end data and support data-model QA (day-to-day querying; deeper SQL is a growth path here).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform regression testing with awareness of cross-module system impact; estimate, prioritize, plan, and coordinate testing activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test current products, identify deficiencies, and proactively suggest solutions and process improvements that shorten test cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with software engineering, following best practices with a focus on improving test coverage; contribute clear status reports on automation progress, issues, and risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What we are looking for:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;College degree or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3–5 years&lt;/strong&gt; of experience in software QA methodologies, tools, and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of software QA best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in an &lt;strong&gt;Agile/Scrum&lt;/strong&gt; development process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hands-on Playwright&lt;/strong&gt; (or equivalent modern automation framework, e.g. Selenium/Cypress) with a clear willingness to work primarily in Playwright.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fluency with AI coding/testing assistants&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g. GitHub Copilot, Cursor, Claude) for test generation and debugging — and the judgment to verify their output.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working (intermediate) SQL&lt;/strong&gt; and comfort querying relational databases (PostgreSQL) — you&#39;ll write queries regularly; advanced SQL is a plus, not a screen-out.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate English level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal and communication skills; a genuine team player.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
